⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Miles Teg
node D1 · D1 · ⟦Miles Teg:D1:70c50e⟧

WHO   — Miles Teg — the Bashar, the Sisterhood's shield
WHAT  — The greatest military commander of his age, a Bashar in the service of the Bene Gesserit and a descendant of Duncan Idaho.
WHERE — D1 · Dune  Framework inputs: The late saga — Heretics of Dune and Chapterhouse: Dune, the Bene Gesserit's most dangerous age  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — He is the soldier the Sisterhood needs to survive an enemy it can barely see, in the most perilous hour of its long history.
HOW   — Old, brilliant, and unshakably loyal, he guards the latest Duncan ghola and, under mortal threat, awakens hidden powers.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The old soldier who, when death came, ran faster than sight and saw the ships that hid from the universe.

